# enpass-mcp optional configuration.
# Preferred: store master passwords in the OS keychain via `enpass-mcp add-vault`.
# The variables below are optional.
#
# IMPORTANT: never commit a real password. The server also reads an optional
# ".env" from its config directory (e.g. ~/Library/Application Support/enpass-mcp/.env
# on macOS), which lives OUTSIDE this repository. Put any real secret there, not here.

# Override the config directory (default: OS-specific app config dir).
# ENPASS_MCP_CONFIG_DIR=/custom/path/enpass-mcp

# Optional shared master password used for any vault without a keychain entry.
# Convenient for autonomous access when all vaults share one passphrase, but less
# secure than the keychain (plaintext on disk). Keep it in the config-dir .env.
# ENPASS_MASTER_PASSWORD=

# Optional per-vault override (vault name uppercased), takes precedence:
# ENPASS_MASTER_PASSWORD_PRIMARY=
